1
00:04:56,430 --> 00:04:57,430
No!

2
00:05:31,350 --> 00:05:33,430
There she is.
There she is.

3
00:05:42,940 --> 00:05:44,440
There she is.

4
00:14:32,890 --> 00:14:34,890
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,</i>

5
00:14:34,890 --> 00:14:39,390
<i>I've traveled over
half our state
to be here tonight.</i>

6
00:14:39,400 --> 00:14:41,910
<i>I couldn't get away sooner
because my new well
was coming in</i>

7
00:14:41,900 --> 00:14:44,900
<i>at Coyote Hills
and I had to see about it.</i>

8
00:14:44,900 --> 00:14:47,900
<i>That well is now flowing
at 2,000 barrels</i>

9
00:14:47,900 --> 00:14:51,910
<i>and it's paying me
an income of $5,000 a week.</i>

10
00:14:51,910 --> 00:14:55,410
I have two others drilling
and I have 16 producing
at Antelope,

11
00:14:55,410 --> 00:14:59,910
so, ladies and gentlemen,
if I say I'm an oilman,
you will agree.

12
00:15:02,420 --> 00:15:05,420
Now, you have
a great chance here,

13
00:15:05,420 --> 00:15:08,420
but bear in mind
you could lose it all
if you're not careful.

14
00:15:08,420 --> 00:15:10,840
Out of all men
that beg for a chance
to drill your lots,

15
00:15:10,840 --> 00:15:14,350
maybe one in 20
will be oilmen.

16
00:15:14,350 --> 00:15:15,350
The rest will be
speculators,

17
00:15:15,850 --> 00:15:18,350
that's men trying
to get between you
and the oilmen

18
00:15:18,350 --> 00:15:21,850
to get some of
the money that ought,
by rights, come to you.

19
00:15:21,850 --> 00:15:24,860
Even if you find
one that has money
and means to drill,

20
00:15:24,860 --> 00:15:27,360
he'll maybe know
nothing about drilling.

21
00:15:27,360 --> 00:15:29,360
He'll have to
hire the job out
on contract,

22
00:15:29,360 --> 00:15:32,360
and then you're
depending on
a contractor,

23
00:15:32,360 --> 00:15:33,860
who'll rush
the job through

24
00:15:33,870 --> 00:15:35,880
so he can get
another contract
just as quick as he can.

25
00:15:35,870 --> 00:15:37,370
This is the way
that this works.

26
00:15:37,370 --> 00:15:40,370
What is your offer?
We're wasting time.

27
00:15:41,370 --> 00:15:42,370
Please!

28
00:15:45,380 --> 00:15:47,880
I do my own drilling.

29
00:15:47,880 --> 00:15:51,920
And the men that work
for me, work for me,
and they are men I know.

30
00:15:51,920 --> 00:15:55,920
I make it
my business to be there
and to see their work.

31
00:15:55,920 --> 00:15:58,920
I don't lose my tools in
the hole and spend months
fishing for them.

32
00:15:58,920 --> 00:15:59,920
I don't botch
the cementing off

33
00:16:00,430 --> 00:16:03,940
and let water in the hole
and ruin the whole lease.

34
00:16:03,930 --> 00:16:05,900
I'm a family man.

35
00:16:05,900 --> 00:16:07,400
I run a family business.

36
00:16:07,400 --> 00:16:09,900
This is my son
and my partner,
H.W. Plainview.

37
00:16:11,400 --> 00:16:16,410
We offer you the bond
of family that very few
oilmen can understand.

38
00:16:18,410 --> 00:16:21,410
I'm fixed like
no other company
in this field

39
00:16:21,410 --> 00:16:24,920
and that's because
my Coyote Hills well
has just come in.

40
00:16:24,920 --> 00:16:27,420
I have a string of tools
all ready to put to work.

41
00:16:27,420 --> 00:16:29,420
I can load a rig onto trucks
and have them here in a week.

42
00:16:29,920 --> 00:16:32,920
I have business connections,
so I can get the lumber
for the derricks.

43
00:16:32,930 --> 00:16:36,940
Such things go by friendship
in a rush like this.

44
00:16:36,930 --> 00:16:40,930
And this is why
I can guarantee
to start drilling

45
00:16:40,930 --> 00:16:43,930
and to put up
the cash to
back my word.

46
00:16:43,940 --> 00:16:45,450
I assure you,
ladies and gentlemen,

47
00:16:45,440 --> 00:16:48,940
no matter what
the others promise to do,

48
00:16:48,940 --> 00:16:51,940
when it comes
to the showdown,
they won't be there.

49
00:16:53,450 --> 00:16:57,460
Sit down! Sit down,
you have no right...

50
00:16:57,450 --> 00:16:59,570
Let us discuss
what the man has to say.

51
00:16:59,570 --> 00:17:01,070
Prescott, do you
trust this man?

52
00:17:01,570 --> 00:17:02,570
Let's discuss
what he has to say.

53
00:17:02,570 --> 00:17:04,570
There's logic
to what he's saying.

54
00:17:04,570 --> 00:17:08,130
How does he know?
My lot is there!

55
00:17:08,130 --> 00:17:11,130
Two or three years,
it could be ten years!

56
00:17:11,130 --> 00:17:13,130
We gain nothing
by losing our heads!

57
00:17:13,130 --> 00:17:14,630
Look at that
well out there!

58
00:17:14,630 --> 00:17:17,130
Nobody's
losing their heads.

59
00:17:17,140 --> 00:17:19,650
You have no business
being here!

60
00:17:20,640 --> 00:17:23,310
Sit that woman down, sir!

61
00:17:24,810 --> 00:17:26,310
You can sit down.

62
00:17:26,310 --> 00:17:29,980
Mr. Plainview!
Please, Mr. Plainview.

63
00:17:29,980 --> 00:17:31,980
No, Mr. Plainview!
No, where are you going?

64
00:17:31,980 --> 00:17:33,480
I don't need
the lease. Thank you.

65
00:17:33,490 --> 00:17:35,000
But we need you.

66
00:17:34,990 --> 00:17:37,490
Too much confusion.
Thank you for your time.

67
00:17:37,490 --> 00:17:38,990
No, no, there's
no confusion.

68
00:17:39,490 --> 00:17:42,990
I wouldn't take
the lease if you
gave it to me as a gift.

69
00:17:53,510 --> 00:17:56,520
<i>Mr. Bankside,
I'm not going to
waste your time.</i>

70
00:17:56,510 --> 00:17:59,010
<i>I'd certainly appreciate it
if you didn't waste mine.</i>

71
00:17:59,010 --> 00:18:03,630
Now, if you wish to sign with
me, we can have a well
drilling within 10 days.

72
00:18:04,130 --> 00:18:07,630
Your lot is
further north from
the discovery well up here.

73
00:18:07,640 --> 00:18:10,200
That means
we'll probably
have to dig deeper.

74
00:18:10,190 --> 00:18:12,690
And if there's as much oil
here as I think there is,

75
00:18:12,690 --> 00:18:15,690
it'll be harder to reach,
but once we find it,
we can take it right out.

76
00:18:15,690 --> 00:18:20,200
We have to act quickly,
because very soon
these fields will be dry.

77
00:18:20,700 --> 00:18:22,700
I need you to know
what you want to do.

78
00:18:22,700 --> 00:18:26,200
Now, because of the distance
from the discovery well,

79
00:18:26,200 --> 00:18:28,210
I'll pay you
a smaller royalty
than you'd get down there

80
00:18:28,210 --> 00:18:32,210
but I'm prepared to give you
a $1,000 bonus on your lot.

81
00:18:32,210 --> 00:18:33,710
What kind of royalty
are you talking about?

82
00:18:34,210 --> 00:18:38,720
One-sixth,
plus a guarantee to start
drilling within 10 days.

83
00:18:38,720 --> 00:18:41,720
Now, that's something
you won't find
anywhere else.

84
00:18:50,730 --> 00:18:52,730
What age are
your children, ma'am?

85
00:18:52,730 --> 00:18:55,400
Ten and twelve.

86
00:18:55,400 --> 00:18:59,770
Mr. Plainview,
a question, sir.
Where is your wife?

87
00:19:01,740 --> 00:19:04,740
She died in childbirth,
Mrs. Bankside.

88
00:19:05,740 --> 00:19:07,740
So it's just me
and my son now.

89
00:19:14,840 --> 00:19:16,620
It's coming in, boss!

90
00:19:17,120 --> 00:19:18,620
Hear it?

91
00:19:44,730 --> 00:19:46,230
Mr. Plainview?

92
00:19:46,230 --> 00:19:47,730
Yes?

93
00:19:49,740 --> 00:19:52,240
Are you Daniel Plainview?

94
00:19:53,740 --> 00:19:55,240
Yes.

95
00:19:56,750 --> 00:19:58,760
What can I
do for you?

96
00:20:00,750 --> 00:20:02,250
You look for oil.

97
00:20:03,750 --> 00:20:05,250
That's right.

98
00:20:05,250 --> 00:20:08,260
What do you pay for
a place that has it?

99
00:20:08,260 --> 00:20:09,760
Well, that depends.

100
00:20:09,760 --> 00:20:11,260
What does it
depend on?

101
00:20:13,260 --> 00:20:16,260
On a lot of things.

102
00:20:16,260 --> 00:20:21,270
If I told you I knew a place
that had oil where land
could be bought cheaply,

103
00:20:21,270 --> 00:20:24,270
what do you think
that would be worth?

104
00:20:24,770 --> 00:20:25,770
Oh, I think that

105
00:20:27,780 --> 00:20:29,290
you should let me know
what you know

106
00:20:29,280 --> 00:20:32,280
and then we'll try
and work something out.

107
00:20:34,280 --> 00:20:36,700
Can I sit down?
Please.

108
00:20:47,710 --> 00:20:50,210
What church
do you belong to?

109
00:20:55,720 --> 00:20:57,220
I...

110
00:20:59,220 --> 00:21:02,730
I enjoy all faiths.
I don't belong to one
church in particular.

111
00:21:02,730 --> 00:21:06,730
I like them all.
I like everything.
Where are you from?

112
00:21:07,230 --> 00:21:08,230
That would be
telling you.

113
00:21:08,730 --> 00:21:10,230
That's what I
want to sell you.

114
00:21:13,240 --> 00:21:16,240
What are you
doing in Signal Hill?

115
00:21:16,240 --> 00:21:18,740
We have oil,
and it seeps
through the ground.

116
00:21:18,740 --> 00:21:20,240
Do you want to pay me
to know where it is?

117
00:21:20,250 --> 00:21:21,760
Just 'cause
there's something
on the ground

118
00:21:21,750 --> 00:21:23,250
doesn't mean
there's anything
beneath it.

119
00:21:23,250 --> 00:21:26,250
Why did Standard Oil
buy up land?

120
00:21:28,750 --> 00:21:30,750
Is it in California?

121
00:21:31,260 --> 00:21:33,270
Maybe.

122
00:21:33,260 --> 00:21:34,760
How much land
did they buy?

123
00:21:34,760 --> 00:21:38,180
I'd like it better
if you didn't think
I was stupid.

124
00:21:46,690 --> 00:21:49,190
Why did you
come to me?

125
00:21:49,190 --> 00:21:51,190
You just brought
this well in.

126
00:21:51,190 --> 00:21:53,190
That's right.

127
00:21:53,200 --> 00:21:57,710
Yes, so just give me
$500 in cash right now

128
00:21:57,700 --> 00:22:00,200
and I'll tell you
where it is.

129
00:22:00,200 --> 00:22:02,700
I'll tell you
what I'll do, son.
I'll give you $100 now,

130
00:22:02,700 --> 00:22:07,710
and if it proves to
be a promising lease,
then give you a $1,000 bonus.

131
00:22:07,710 --> 00:22:09,680
Six hundred dollars.

132
00:22:12,180 --> 00:22:13,680
Tell me one thing
to help me decide.

133
00:22:13,680 --> 00:22:15,180
What else have you
got up there?

134
00:22:15,180 --> 00:22:16,800
What do you grow?

135
00:22:17,300 --> 00:22:20,800
We have a big ranch,
but it's mostly rocks.

136
00:22:20,810 --> 00:22:23,320
Plant things.
Nothing will grow
but weeds.

137
00:22:23,310 --> 00:22:24,690
What makes
you think it's up?

138
00:22:24,690 --> 00:22:28,150
Is there sulfur around?
Or alkali deposits?

139
00:22:28,150 --> 00:22:31,370
Alkali nearby.
I don't know sulfur.

140
00:22:37,790 --> 00:22:39,290
Is that your son?

141
00:22:39,790 --> 00:22:41,290
Yes.

142
00:22:42,330 --> 00:22:43,830
Hi.
        Hi.

143
00:22:47,170 --> 00:22:50,090
Who are you?
I'm Fletcher Hamilton.

144
00:22:50,090 --> 00:22:52,100
Nice to meet you, son.
What's your name?

145
00:22:52,090 --> 00:22:53,590
What do you do?

146
00:22:54,590 --> 00:22:56,890
I work with
Mr. Plainview.

147
00:22:57,390 --> 00:22:59,390
Here's $500, son.

148
00:22:59,390 --> 00:23:03,400
You tell me
something worth hearing,
this money's yours.

149
00:23:06,940 --> 00:23:10,950
I come from a town
called Little Boston
in Isabella County.

150
00:23:13,070 --> 00:23:17,580
This is us, here.
Spur station here
at Little Boston.

151
00:23:17,580 --> 00:23:20,580
The Sunday ranch
is what you're
looking for.

152
00:23:21,080 --> 00:23:23,080
There's a sheep trail
that takes you there.

153
00:23:23,080 --> 00:23:26,090
It's a mile out of town
headed west, not far.

154
00:23:26,090 --> 00:23:30,090
Just through a small pass here
near the base of the hills.

155
00:23:30,090 --> 00:23:34,090
You'll pass a church
and just follow
the sheep trail.

156
00:23:34,100 --> 00:23:36,110
Where's Standard
buying up?

157
00:23:36,100 --> 00:23:38,100
Here and here.

158
00:23:40,600 --> 00:23:43,100
Your family name
is Sunday, yes?
            That's right.

159
00:23:43,100 --> 00:23:44,600
How many's
in your family?

160
00:23:44,610 --> 00:23:48,120
My father and
mother and sisters
and my brother Eli.

161
00:23:48,110 --> 00:23:50,610
How many sisters
do you have?
      Two.

162
00:23:50,610 --> 00:23:53,110
What's your name?
                 Paul.

163
00:23:53,110 --> 00:23:56,620
Does any of your family
know about the oil that
you say is there?

164
00:23:56,620 --> 00:23:58,120
I don't know.

165
00:23:58,120 --> 00:24:00,620
My uncle always said
there was oil there,

166
00:24:00,620 --> 00:24:03,120
but I don't know
what they heard
or what they think.

167
00:24:03,120 --> 00:24:04,620
What do you grow?

168
00:24:04,630 --> 00:24:07,140
It's goats.
It's a goat farm.

169
00:24:07,130 --> 00:24:10,130
I told you,
nothing grows
but weeds.

170
00:24:10,130 --> 00:24:12,630
Is there water?
         It's salty.

171
00:24:12,630 --> 00:24:16,050
You drill a well,
it's hard not
to get saltwater.

172
00:24:18,060 --> 00:24:21,570
The oil is there.
I'm telling you.

173
00:24:26,060 --> 00:24:29,570
I want to go now, so...
You can stay tonight.

174
00:24:29,570 --> 00:24:31,570
No, I want to go now.
I want to leave.

175
00:24:31,570 --> 00:24:35,070
Listen, Paul.

176
00:24:35,570 --> 00:24:40,080
If I travel all the way
out there and I find that
you've been lying to me,

177
00:24:40,080 --> 00:24:43,080
I'm going to find you
and I'm going to take
more than my money back.

178
00:24:43,080 --> 00:24:45,080
Is that all right
with you?

179
00:24:45,080 --> 00:24:48,080
Yes, sir.
All right, then.

180
00:24:48,090 --> 00:24:50,100
Nice luck to you.
God bless.

181
00:24:50,090 --> 00:24:52,090
And to you,
young man.

182
00:26:31,690 --> 00:26:33,690
- There's someone coming.
- Thank you, Mary.

183
00:26:43,700 --> 00:26:45,700
Good evening.

184
00:26:45,700 --> 00:26:47,200
Good evening.

185
00:26:49,710 --> 00:26:53,710
My name's Daniel Plainview.
This is my son, H.W.

186
00:26:53,710 --> 00:26:56,710
Are you hunting?
Hunting for quail.

187
00:26:56,710 --> 00:26:59,720
We're told there might be
a good place to camp up
near the Sunday ranch.

188
00:26:59,720 --> 00:27:01,720
This is the Sunday ranch.
You can camp here.

189
00:27:01,720 --> 00:27:05,010
Thank you.
Do you have water?
              Yes.

190
00:27:05,510 --> 00:27:07,510
We heard
there was an earthquake
up here a few days ago.

191
00:27:07,510 --> 00:27:09,510
Is that right?
Yes.

192
00:27:10,010 --> 00:27:11,510
Your family?

193
00:27:11,510 --> 00:27:13,510
Yeah, all fine.
Thank you.

194
00:27:15,520 --> 00:27:17,020
We have goat's milk,
if you'd like.

195
00:27:17,020 --> 00:27:18,520
That would be fine.

196
00:27:21,020 --> 00:27:22,020
Now,

197
00:27:23,530 --> 00:27:26,040
if we set our tent
away over there,

198
00:27:26,030 --> 00:27:28,030
we'd be out of
your way over there.

199
00:27:28,030 --> 00:27:29,030
That's fine.

200
00:27:29,530 --> 00:27:31,530
Ruth! Help these men
and bring them some water.

201
00:27:31,530 --> 00:27:33,030
No! H.W.

202
00:27:35,040 --> 00:27:38,540
Mr. Plainview,
would you like
that milk now?

203
00:27:38,540 --> 00:27:40,040
That would be fine.
Thank you.

204
00:27:40,040 --> 00:27:42,540
Mary! Bring them
some milk.

205
00:27:42,540 --> 00:27:44,040
My family will
help you set up
your tent.

206
00:27:44,050 --> 00:27:46,560
No, please.
We set ourselves on
this camping trip.

207
00:27:46,550 --> 00:27:48,550
We have to do
the camping.

208
00:27:48,550 --> 00:27:50,050
Hurry up!

209
00:27:52,550 --> 00:27:54,550
Do you have bread?

210
00:27:55,060 --> 00:27:57,060
We have potatoes.

211
00:27:57,060 --> 00:27:58,560
Potatoes would be nice,
thank you.

212
00:27:58,560 --> 00:28:00,060
I'll have them
boil you up
some potatoes.

213
00:28:00,060 --> 00:28:02,560
That's all right.
I thought maybe
we'd make a fire.

214
00:28:02,560 --> 00:28:05,070
I wanted to work
with my son on
making a fire.

215
00:28:05,070 --> 00:28:06,980
All right. My son,
Eli, will bring you
some wood.

216
00:28:06,990 --> 00:28:09,000
Thank you so much
for your hospitality,
Mr. Sunday.

217
00:28:08,990 --> 00:28:09,990
Yes.

218
00:28:10,490 --> 00:28:11,490
And we'll be
out of your way.

219
00:28:11,490 --> 00:28:13,990
We're just hunting
        for quail.
Yes.

220
00:28:15,990 --> 00:28:18,500
I'm sorry we
don't have any bread.
                 No, no, no.

221
00:28:18,500 --> 00:28:21,000
Corn doesn't fill out
in the hills here.
It's mostly rock.

222
00:28:21,500 --> 00:28:24,000
We don't have room
to raise the grain.

223
00:28:28,010 --> 00:28:30,020
Thank you,
young lady.

224
00:28:55,080 --> 00:28:56,580
My name is Eli.

225
00:28:58,090 --> 00:29:00,100
Yes, you're Eli Sunday.

226
00:29:01,090 --> 00:29:02,590
Welcome.

227
00:29:06,090 --> 00:29:08,090
H.W.
  Eli.

228
00:29:13,100 --> 00:29:14,600
You're hunting quail?

229
00:29:14,600 --> 00:29:16,100
That's right.

230
00:29:20,610 --> 00:29:22,610
We will bring dinner.

231
00:29:22,610 --> 00:29:24,610
Thank you.
Thank you so much.

232
00:30:46,980 --> 00:30:48,980
Dad!

233
00:30:48,980 --> 00:30:50,980
Dad, look at my shoe.

234
00:31:17,010 --> 00:31:20,010
That's earthquake oil.
Set loose.

235
00:31:43,580 --> 00:31:44,580
<i>So...</i>

236
00:31:46,090 --> 00:31:47,590
<i>So?</i>

237
00:31:48,590 --> 00:31:50,590
<i>So, so.</i>

238
00:31:50,590 --> 00:31:54,680
<i>If there's anything here,
we take it to the sea.</i>

239
00:31:55,180 --> 00:31:58,680
What we do is we build
a pipeline to Port Hueneme
or Santa Paula,

240
00:31:58,680 --> 00:32:00,180
it's about 100 miles,

241
00:32:00,690 --> 00:32:04,860
