Henry.

733
01:18:18,480 --> 01:18:20,480
Mary Branch?
Is that your mother?

734
01:18:20,980 --> 01:18:22,980
Yes, sir,
that's right.

735
01:18:24,980 --> 01:18:30,490
I read about your
gusher in the paper,
about your success.

736
01:18:30,490 --> 01:18:33,490
You heard
about my strike?
You just show up?

737
01:18:34,490 --> 01:18:36,410
Our father's dead.

738
01:18:37,910 --> 01:18:41,420
Ernest died, I heard.
I wanted to find you.

739
01:18:41,420 --> 01:18:42,920
When?

740
01:18:42,920 --> 01:18:46,420
Three months ago.
I got a letter
from Annabelle.

741
01:18:47,420 --> 01:18:49,420
My sister,
Annabelle?

742
01:18:51,430 --> 01:18:52,930
Where is she?

743
01:18:53,430 --> 01:18:54,930
Still at home.
Fond du Lac.

744
01:18:56,930 --> 01:19:00,430
You came all the way
from Wisconsin to
tell me this?

745
01:19:00,440 --> 01:19:03,450
I'm coming from
New Mexico.
I've been there.

746
01:19:04,940 --> 01:19:06,440
I came to find you.

747
01:19:07,940 --> 01:19:09,940
Did you know about me?

748
01:19:17,950 --> 01:19:20,960
Do you have
identification?

749
01:19:20,960 --> 01:19:22,960
Do you have
this letter?

750
01:19:46,230 --> 01:19:48,230
Where are you
          coming from?
From New Mexico.

751
01:19:48,230 --> 01:19:50,820
Yes, I know,
but from where?

752
01:19:50,820 --> 01:19:54,820
Silver City.
I've been there
for two years.

753
01:19:54,820 --> 01:19:59,830
I was trying drilling
of my own for years.

754
01:19:59,830 --> 01:20:04,330
Getting leases in Texas.
Louisiana.

755
01:20:04,330 --> 01:20:06,330
Anything that produced?

756
01:20:06,340 --> 01:20:09,350
No.
Not like your success, no.

757
01:20:15,760 --> 01:20:18,600
Are you married?
No.

758
01:20:18,600 --> 01:20:23,600
I spent time in jail.
I had a stretch of
very bad time.

759
01:20:23,600 --> 01:20:28,110
I had nothing.
I was picked up
in Louisiana.

760
01:20:28,110 --> 01:20:32,110
I worked on a chain gang
for six months
building roads.

761
01:20:32,610 --> 01:20:35,610
That was a very hard time.

762
01:20:39,120 --> 01:20:41,120
Are you married?

763
01:20:42,620 --> 01:20:45,070
What were you
in jail for?

764
01:20:45,070 --> 01:20:49,580
Believe it or not,
for all the terrible things
I've gotten myself into,

765
01:20:49,580 --> 01:20:53,080
when they picked me up,
I hadn't done anything.

766
01:20:53,080 --> 01:20:57,080
But I've done
my share of things

767
01:20:59,090 --> 01:21:01,590
that shouldn't
be talked about.

768
01:21:24,410 --> 01:21:27,410
Drink it.
Drink it!

769
01:22:10,040 --> 01:22:11,040
Come on.

770
01:22:42,740 --> 01:22:44,240
So...

771
01:22:48,750 --> 01:22:50,750
What do you want, Henry?

772
01:22:53,250 --> 01:22:54,750
Nothing.

773
01:22:57,760 --> 01:22:59,760
If you can
spare something,

774
01:22:59,760 --> 01:23:01,760
I can work for
you in any way.

775
01:23:01,760 --> 01:23:07,260
I know I'll keep moving,
before long, to get back
to Fond du Lac.

776
01:23:07,270 --> 01:23:09,780
Do you have
any money?
                        Some.

777
01:23:10,770 --> 01:23:12,770
Not much.
Just answer me directly.

778
01:23:12,770 --> 01:23:16,770
You say "nothing,"
then you say you'd
like to stay and work.

779
01:23:16,780 --> 01:23:21,790
And it's better, I'd just
like to hear you say
you'd like to be here.

780
01:23:22,780 --> 01:23:24,780
I'd like to be here.

781
01:23:30,210 --> 01:23:35,720
I'm a good worker.
I worked cable tool rigs,
built railroads.

782
01:23:37,710 --> 01:23:39,710
I won't need any favors.

783
01:23:44,720 --> 01:23:46,220
Good.

784
01:24:11,580 --> 01:24:13,860
<i>What did
my mother know?</i>

785
01:24:16,370 --> 01:24:18,670
<i>I don't know.</i>

786
01:24:18,670 --> 01:24:23,370
<i>I don't know if she knew
and looked the other way,
if she never knew.</i>

787
01:24:25,880 --> 01:24:27,880
<i>Why did you leave?</i>

788
01:24:29,880 --> 01:24:32,880
<i>I know you didn't
get on with our father.</i>

789
01:24:38,190 --> 01:24:41,690
I worked for
Geological Survey
and went to Kansas.

790
01:24:44,200 --> 01:24:47,210
I couldn't stay there.
I just couldn't.

791
01:24:48,700 --> 01:24:51,700
I don't like to
explain myself.

792
01:24:57,710 --> 01:24:59,710
Are you an
angry man, Henry?

793
01:25:00,210 --> 01:25:02,710
About what?

794
01:25:02,710 --> 01:25:06,220
Are you envious?
Do you get envious?

795
01:25:07,720 --> 01:25:09,640
I don't think so, no.

796
01:25:14,140 --> 01:25:16,640
I have a competition in me.

797
01:25:17,650 --> 01:25:20,160
I want no one else
to succeed.

798
01:25:25,150 --> 01:25:27,150
I hate most people.

799
01:25:27,160 --> 01:25:29,670
That part of me
is gone.

800
01:25:30,660 --> 01:25:33,660
Working and not succeeding,

801
01:25:33,660 --> 01:25:37,660
all my failures
have left me...

802
01:25:40,670 --> 01:25:42,670
I just don't care.

803
01:25:44,170 --> 01:25:48,680
Well, if it's in me,
it's in you.

804
01:25:48,680 --> 01:25:54,180
There are times when
I look at people and
I see nothing worth liking.

805
01:25:59,690 --> 01:26:04,190
I want to earn enough money
I can get away from everyone.

806
01:26:09,110 --> 01:26:11,620
What will you do
about your boy?

807
01:26:19,120 --> 01:26:20,620
I don't know.

808
01:26:22,630 --> 01:26:25,130
Maybe it'll change.

809
01:26:25,130 --> 01:26:27,630
Does your sound
come back to you?
I don't know.

810
01:26:27,630 --> 01:26:29,630
Maybe no one knows that.

811
01:26:29,630 --> 01:26:31,640
Doctor might not know that.

812
01:26:31,640 --> 01:26:33,640
Where's his mother?

813
01:26:39,640 --> 01:26:42,650
I don't want to talk
about those things.

814
01:26:46,150 --> 01:26:48,150
I see the worst
in people, Henry.

815
01:26:50,160 --> 01:26:54,170
I don't need to
look past seeing them
to get all I need.

816
01:26:56,160 --> 01:27:00,160
I've built up my
hatreds over the years,
little by little.

817
01:27:04,170 --> 01:27:07,170
Having you here gives me
a second breath of life.

818
01:27:08,670 --> 01:27:11,170
I can't keep
doing this on my own

819
01:27:14,680 --> 01:27:19,680
with these people.

820
01:27:59,390 --> 01:28:01,840
Daniel! Daniel,
wake up! Daniel!

821
01:29:39,570 --> 01:29:40,570
Uh...

822
01:29:44,080 --> 01:29:47,580
Just have to go
and have a word
with the conductor.

823
01:29:48,580 --> 01:29:50,580
I'll be right back.

824
01:29:50,590 --> 01:29:55,600
You stay here.
You understand?
You stay here.

825
01:29:56,590 --> 01:29:58,590
I'll be right back.

826
01:30:50,100 --> 01:30:50,820
H.W.!

827
01:30:50,810 --> 01:30:52,930
No! No!

828
01:30:54,430 --> 01:30:55,930
No!

829
01:31:05,440 --> 01:31:07,440
Tilford!
         Plainview.

830
01:31:07,450 --> 01:31:09,460
This is my brother,
Henry Plainview
from Fond du Lac.

831
01:31:09,950 --> 01:31:11,450
H.M. Tilford.
Pleasure.

832
01:31:11,450 --> 01:31:13,950
Henry Plainview.
J.J. Carter.

833
01:31:15,950 --> 01:31:17,450
So...

834
01:31:17,460 --> 01:31:18,970
Shall we?
Yes.

835
01:31:27,470 --> 01:31:28,890
How's your boy?

836
01:31:29,880 --> 01:31:30,880
Thank you for asking.

837
01:31:30,890 --> 01:31:32,900
Is there anything
we can do?

838
01:31:33,390 --> 01:31:35,270
Thanks for asking
is enough.

839
01:31:37,280 --> 01:31:39,150
So what are your plans?

840
01:31:41,150 --> 01:31:44,160
Is this about buying up
my tracts here?

841
01:31:44,150 --> 01:31:45,650
Yes.

842
01:31:45,650 --> 01:31:48,290
The cable was about
my Coyote Hills lease.

843
01:31:48,290 --> 01:31:50,290
We'd like that, too.

844
01:31:50,290 --> 01:31:52,790
What's your offer
on Coyote Hills?

845
01:31:52,790 --> 01:31:55,040
We'll offer
150,000 for
full title.

846
01:31:55,040 --> 01:31:58,040
That's a deal.
What's next?

847
01:31:58,050 --> 01:32:02,890
You have 11,000 acres
in Little Boston.
You have one proven well

848
01:32:02,880 --> 01:32:04,330
that was damaged...
I have three wells proven.

849
01:32:04,340 --> 01:32:08,850
You haven't been
paying attention.
That's three proven wells.

850
01:32:12,840 --> 01:32:14,840
We'll make you a millionaire
while you're sitting here

851
01:32:14,850 --> 01:32:17,360
from one minute
to the next.

852
01:32:18,850 --> 01:32:21,850
And what else
would I do
with myself?

853
01:32:23,350 --> 01:32:25,360
Are you asking me?

854
01:32:25,360 --> 01:32:27,360
What else
would I do
with myself?

855
01:32:28,360 --> 01:32:30,860
Take care of your son.

856
01:32:32,360 --> 01:32:34,860
I don't know
what you would do.

857
01:32:37,290 --> 01:32:39,800
If you were me
and Standard offered
to buy what you had

858
01:32:39,790 --> 01:32:42,540
for a million dollars,
why? So, why?

859
01:32:44,040 --> 01:32:45,540
You know why.

860
01:32:45,540 --> 01:32:47,040
Yeah, you fellas
should just scratch
around in the dirt

861
01:32:47,050 --> 01:32:48,050
and find it like
the rest of us,

862
01:32:48,550 --> 01:32:50,550
instead of buying up
someone else's hard work.

863
01:32:50,550 --> 01:32:52,720
I've scratched
around the dirt, son.

864
01:32:52,720 --> 01:32:54,720
You going to change
your shipping costs?

865
01:32:54,720 --> 01:32:56,220
We don't dictate
shipping costs.

866
01:32:56,220 --> 01:32:57,720
That's railroad business.

867
01:32:57,720 --> 01:33:00,720
Oh, you don't
own the railroads?

868
01:33:05,230 --> 01:33:08,230
'Course you do.
Of course you do.

869
01:33:09,730 --> 01:33:12,240
Where you going
to put it all?

870
01:33:13,240 --> 01:33:14,740
Where?

871
01:33:16,240 --> 01:33:20,740
Build a pipeline?
Make a deal with
Union Oil? Be my guest.

872
01:33:20,750 --> 01:33:22,260
But if you
can't pull it off,

873
01:33:22,250 --> 01:33:27,330
you've got an ocean
of oil under your feet
with nowhere to go.

874
01:33:27,340 --> 01:33:32,350
Why not turn it over to us?
We'll make you rich.

875
01:33:32,340 --> 01:33:34,340
You spend time
with your boy.

876
01:33:35,840 --> 01:33:37,840
It's a great discovery.

877
01:33:38,850 --> 01:33:40,850
Now, let us help you.

878
01:33:50,160 --> 01:33:53,160
Did you just tell me
how to run my family?

879
01:33:53,160 --> 01:33:55,660
It might be more
important now that
you've proven the field

880
01:33:55,660 --> 01:33:57,660
and we're offering
to buy you out.

881
01:33:57,670 --> 01:33:59,680
One night
I'm going to come to you,
inside of your house,

882
01:33:59,670 --> 01:34:02,920
or wherever you're sleeping,
and I'm going to
cut your throat.

883
01:34:02,920 --> 01:34:04,920
What?

884
01:34:04,920 --> 01:34:06,290
What are you talking about?
Have you gone crazy?

885
01:34:06,290 --> 01:34:07,790
Did you hear
  what I said?
I heard what you said,

886
01:34:07,790 --> 01:34:10,290
why did you say it?
You don't tell me
about my son.

887
01:34:10,300 --> 01:34:12,310
Why are you acting insane
and threatening
to cut my throat?

888
01:34:12,800 --> 01:34:15,850
You don't tell
           me about my son.
I'm not telling you anything!

889
01:34:15,850 --> 01:34:16,850
I'm asking you
to be reasonable.

890
01:34:17,350 --> 01:34:19,690
If I've offended you,
I apologize.

891
01:34:19,690 --> 01:34:21,720
You'll see what I can do.

892
01:34:29,500 --> 01:34:33,980
This parcel here is
the 3,000-acre ranch
owned by B.L. Harper.

893
01:34:33,990 --> 01:34:36,500
This is San Luis
Obispo County land.

894
01:34:36,490 --> 01:34:38,490
And from here to the coast,
it's all Union Oil.

895
01:34:38,490 --> 01:34:41,490
What's this?
Why don't I own this?

896
01:34:44,500 --> 01:34:47,010
Why don't I own this?

897
01:34:47,000 --> 01:34:50,000
That's the Bandy tract.

898
01:34:50,000 --> 01:34:53,000
He was the holdout,
when we were
doing the buying.

899
01:34:53,500 --> 01:34:55,510
He had hoped to
speak with you.

900
01:35:00,010 --> 01:35:03,510
Can't you just
build the pipeline
around this tract?

901
01:35:06,520 --> 01:35:10,520
Can I build around 50 miles
of Tehachapi mountains?

902
01:35:10,520 --> 01:35:13,520
Don't be thick in
front of me, Al.

903
01:35:13,520 --> 01:35:17,530
I can go to him again.
    No, I'll go and talk
    to the man.

904
01:35:17,530 --> 01:35:20,530
I'll talk to him.
Show you how it's done.

905
01:35:24,540 --> 01:35:27,050
All right.
Pack it up, Henry.

906
01:35:36,880 --> 01:35:38,880
How big is his room?

907
01:35:38,880 --> 01:35:40,880
He's sharing
with another boy.

908
01:35:41,390 --> 01:35:43,900
Who?
      An older boy.
      About 12.

909
01:35:43,890 --> 01:35:47,390
He's been there
for a year.
Named Ballard.

910
01:35:52,400 --> 01:35:53,400
How big is the room?

911
01:35:53,900 --> 01:35:56,900
Oh, it's a fair size.
Got enough space.

912
01:35:58,900 --> 01:36:02,240
Are you taking Henry
with you to meet Union Oil?

913
01:36:15,420 --> 01:36:17,420
Are you the son
of William Bandy?

914
01:36:17,420 --> 01:36:18,920
Grandson.

915
01:36:19,420 --> 01:36:20,920
Is he here?
No, he's out.

916
01:36:20,930 --> 01:36:22,440
Where is he?

917
01:36:22,430 --> 01:36:25,260
Told you, he's out.
Now, what do you want?

918
01:36:28,820 --> 01:36:32,820
I'm Daniel Plainview.
I want to talk with him
about his property.

919
01:36:32,820 --> 01:36:34,820
About what?

920
01:36:34,820 --> 01:36:37,770
I believe I'll talk
with him about that.

921
01:36:38,280 --> 01:36:40,790
You're that oilman,
aren't you?
          That's right.

922
01:36:40,780 --> 01:36:42,530
We don't want you
drilling out here.

923
01:36:42,530 --> 01:36:46,170
I don't want it either.
Now, when will he be back?

924
01:36:46,170 --> 01:36:47,670
Few days.

925
01:36:47,670 --> 01:36:50,040
Tell him I'd like
to speak with him.
Not about drilling.

926
01:36:50,040 --> 01:36:52,540
And I'll be back
in a week.

927
01:39:11,260 --> 01:39:13,260
Put that in a glass case.

928
01:39:14,270 --> 01:39:16,780
Here's to Union Oil.

929
01:39:17,270 --> 01:39:18,270
Hundred miles of pipeline,

930
01:39:18,270 --> 01:39:20,770
and all the independent
producers of this great state.

931
01:39:20,770 --> 01:39:21,520
Cheers.

932
01:39:46,760 --> 01:39:49,630
<i>There's that house
in Fond du Lac</i>

933
01:39:51,640 --> 01:39:54,650
<i>that John Hollister built.
    Do you remember it?
Mmm.</i>

934
01:39:57,780 --> 01:40:01,290
I thought as a boy
that was the most beautiful
house I'd ever seen,

935
01:40:01,280 --> 01:40:03,280
and I wanted it.

936
01:40:03,780 --> 01:40:06,070
I wanted to live in it.

937
01:40:06,070 --> 01:40:07,570
And eat in it.

938
01:40:08,570 --> 01:40:10,070
And clean it.

939
01:40:13,070 --> 01:40:17,580
And even as a boy,
I wanted to have children
to run around in it.

940
01:40:19,210 --> 01:40:21,710
You can have anything you'd
like now, Daniel.

941
01:40:22,720 --> 01:40:24,720
And you should.

942
01:40:25,220 --> 01:40:27,220
Where are you
going to build it?

943
01:40:27,220 --> 01:40:29,720
Here, maybe.
Near the ocean.

944
01:40:32,730 --> 01:40:35,140
Would you make it
look like that house?

945
01:40:40,150 --> 01:40:42,900
I think if I saw
that house now,
it'd make me sick.

946
01:40:50,030 --> 01:40:52,530
We can eat and
get some women.

947
01:40:55,580 --> 01:40:57,580
Take them to
the Peachtree dance.

948
01:41:01,090 --> 01:41:05,040
I say get liquored up
and take them to
the Peachtree dance.

949
01:41:08,050 --> 01:41:09,560
Yeah.

950
01:42:28,380 --> 01:42:30,890
Can I have
some money, please?

951
01:42:37,890 --> 01:42:40,400
Can I have
some money, please?

952
01:43:29,440 --> 01:43:31,940
I want you to
tell me something.

953
01:43:35,940 --> 01:43:37,940
What?

954
01:43:37,950 --> 01:43:41,460
What's the name of the farm
next to the Hill House?

955
01:43:52,380 --> 01:43:56,880
What was the name of the farm
next to the Hill House?

956
01:44:00,890 --> 01:44:03,900
I can't remember...
Who are you?

957
01:44:06,890 --> 01:44:08,390
I'll leave, Daniel.

958
01:44:10,390 --> 01:44:11,890
Who are you?

959
01:44:15,400 --> 01:44:16,730
I'm no one.

960
01:44:17,650 --> 01:44:20,150
Just let me
get up and go.

961
01:44:22,660 --> 01:44:24,660
Do I have a brother?

962
01:44:28,660 --> 01:44:33,670
I met a man
in King City who said
he was your brother.

963
01:44:36,050 --> 01:44:39,560
We were friends
for months.

964
01:44:40,560 --> 01:44:42,560
Working in King City.

965
01:44:45,060 --> 01:44:48,060
And he wanted
to make his way
to you, Daniel.

966
01:44:49,070 --> 01:44:51,070
We didn't have any money.

967
01:44:56,070 --> 01:44:58,570
He died of tuberculosis.

968
01:44:59,580 --> 01:45:01,580
He wasn't harmed.

969
01:45:02,580 --> 01:45:05,080
Wasn't killed,
nothing bad.

970
01:45:06,580 --> 01:45:09,090
But he told me about you,

971
01:45:12,090 --> 01:45:14,590
and I just took his story,

972
01:45:18,100 --> 01:45:20,110
used his diary.

973
01:45:23,600 --> 01:45:24,600
Daniel.

974
01:45:26,100 --> 01:45:29,610
Daniel, I'm your friend.

975
01:45:31,610 --> 01:45:34,110
I'm not trying to hurt you.

976
01:45:34,110 --> 01:45:35,480
Never.

977
01:45:36,480 --> 01:45:38,280
Just survive.

978
01:45:38,650 --> 01:45:39,650
No!

979
01:48:49,670 --> 01:48:51,170
