It's the truth.
You're not my son.
You never have been.

1223
02:13:03,260 --> 02:13:04,760
You're an orphan!

1224
02:13:07,880 --> 02:13:09,880
Did you ever
hear that word?

1225
02:13:11,630 --> 02:13:13,800
Tell him what I said.

1226
02:13:14,300 --> 02:13:17,300
You operated here
today like one.

1227
02:13:18,810 --> 02:13:21,060
I should have seen
this coming.

1228
02:13:22,390 --> 02:13:27,620
I should have known that,
under this all,
these past years

1229
02:13:27,620 --> 02:13:31,120
you've been building
new hate for me,
piece by piece.

1230
02:13:31,120 --> 02:13:34,620
I don't even know
who you are because
you have none of me in you.

1231
02:13:34,620 --> 02:13:37,630
You're someone else's.

1232
02:13:39,160 --> 02:13:42,660
This anger.
Your maliciousness.

1233
02:13:43,500 --> 02:13:46,500
Backwards dealings with me.

1234
02:13:48,500 --> 02:13:52,510
You're an orphan
from a basket in
the middle of the desert.

1235
02:13:54,980 --> 02:13:56,980
And I took you for
no other reason

1236
02:13:56,980 --> 02:13:59,480
than I needed
a sweet face to buy land.

1237
02:14:01,320 --> 02:14:03,320
Did you get that?

1238
02:14:04,320 --> 02:14:06,320
So now you know.

1239
02:14:09,660 --> 02:14:14,110
Look at me!
You're lower
than a bastard.

1240
02:14:33,930 --> 02:14:35,470
Mmm-hmm.

1241
02:14:38,970 --> 02:14:43,470
You have none of me in you.
You're just a bastard
from a basket.

1242
02:14:53,040 --> 02:14:57,550
I thank God
I have none of you in me.

1243
02:15:02,380 --> 02:15:06,880
Not my son.
Just a little piece
of competition.

1244
02:15:08,380 --> 02:15:10,890
Bastard from a basket.

1245
02:15:12,890 --> 02:15:15,390
Bastard from a basket!

1246
02:15:23,400 --> 02:15:26,350
You're a bastard
from a basket!

1247
02:16:28,580 --> 02:16:30,580
<i>Get up, Mr. Daniel.</i>

1248
02:16:35,090 --> 02:16:36,590
<i>Mr. Daniel.</i>

1249
02:16:38,640 --> 02:16:41,140
Mr. Daniel,
you've got a visitor.

1250
02:16:44,650 --> 02:16:46,650
Wake up, Mr. Daniel.

1251
02:16:49,150 --> 02:16:50,650
Sir?

1252
02:17:04,170 --> 02:17:06,180
You can leave us now.

1253
02:17:14,680 --> 02:17:15,680
Daniel.

1254
02:17:19,180 --> 02:17:20,180
Daniel.

1255
02:17:22,600 --> 02:17:26,100
Daniel Plainview,
the house is on fire!

1256
02:17:30,610 --> 02:17:33,610
Brother Daniel,
it's Eli.

1257
02:17:43,620 --> 02:17:47,630
Yes, it is.
Yes, it is.

1258
02:17:49,630 --> 02:17:51,630
I'll make us a drink.

1259
02:17:57,640 --> 02:18:01,140
Oh, your home is a miracle.

1260
02:18:02,640 --> 02:18:04,010
It's beautiful.

1261
02:18:05,010 --> 02:18:07,010
God bless it.

1262
02:18:07,010 --> 02:18:11,020
I've been spreading
His word far and wide.

1263
02:18:12,520 --> 02:18:14,320
Far and wide.

1264
02:18:15,740 --> 02:18:18,740
So much travel for Him.

1265
02:18:23,330 --> 02:18:25,830
I've been working in radio.

1266
02:18:28,500 --> 02:18:33,500
Yes, so much...
So much has been happening.

1267
02:18:33,510 --> 02:18:39,190
To be here and find you
and see you well is wonderful.

1268
02:18:39,180 --> 02:18:41,680
And we have
a chance to catch up.

1269
02:18:54,730 --> 02:18:56,730
No. Thank you so much.

1270
02:19:09,790 --> 02:19:11,290
Oh.

1271
02:19:14,800 --> 02:19:16,800
My brother.

1272
02:19:17,800 --> 02:19:21,300
Daniel, my brother
by marriage.

1273
02:19:23,220 --> 02:19:27,220
We're such old friends.
So much time.

1274
02:19:33,930 --> 02:19:36,930
Things go up,
things go down,

1275
02:19:36,940 --> 02:19:41,450
but at least
the Lord is always around.

1276
02:19:42,770 --> 02:19:45,780
We've seen ups and downs,
haven't we?

1277
02:19:49,360 --> 02:19:52,620
Are things down
for you right now, Eli?

1278
02:19:53,620 --> 02:19:55,120
No. No.

1279
02:19:57,620 --> 02:20:00,120
But I do come
with some sad news.

1280
02:20:02,130 --> 02:20:04,630
Perhaps you remember
Mr. Bandy?

1281
02:20:07,130 --> 02:20:11,390
Mr. Bandy has
passed on to the Lord.

1282
02:20:11,390 --> 02:20:15,390
He lived to be 99 years old,
God bless him.

1283
02:20:15,390 --> 02:20:17,390
Mr. Bandy has a grandson.

1284
02:20:17,390 --> 02:20:20,390
Have you met
his grandson,
William?

1285
02:20:20,400 --> 02:20:24,910
William Bandy is one of
the finest members we have

1286
02:20:24,900 --> 02:20:27,900
at the Church of
the Third Revelation.

1287
02:20:27,900 --> 02:20:30,990
He's eager to
come to Hollywood
to be in movies.

1288
02:20:32,490 --> 02:20:34,490
He is very good-looking.

1289
02:20:37,000 --> 02:20:40,010
And I do think
he will have success.

1290
02:20:40,000 --> 02:20:42,500
That's wonderful.

1291
02:20:44,000 --> 02:20:47,050
Would you like me
to speak with him?

1292
02:20:53,980 --> 02:20:58,980
Daniel, I'm asking
if you'd like
to have business

1293
02:20:58,980 --> 02:21:01,490
with the Church of
the Third Revelation

1294
02:21:01,490 --> 02:21:05,490
in developing this lease
on young Bandy's
1,000-acre tract.

1295
02:21:07,990 --> 02:21:09,990
I'm offering you to drill

1296
02:21:10,000 --> 02:21:13,510
on one of the great
undeveloped fields
of Little Boston.

1297
02:21:13,500 --> 02:21:16,000
I'd be happy to
work with you.

1298
02:21:16,000 --> 02:21:18,000
You would?

1299
02:21:19,000 --> 02:21:22,010
Yes, yes, of course.
That's wonderful.

1300
02:21:22,010 --> 02:21:25,010
But there is
one condition
for this work.

1301
02:21:25,010 --> 02:21:26,510
All right.

1302
02:21:28,510 --> 02:21:32,430
I'd like you to tell me
that you are a false prophet.

1303
02:21:37,560 --> 02:21:40,570
I'd like you to
tell me that you are,

1304
02:21:40,560 --> 02:21:44,060
and have been
a false prophet.

1305
02:21:44,060 --> 02:21:46,560
And that God is
a superstition.

1306
02:21:52,570 --> 02:21:54,820
But that's a lie.

1307
02:21:57,130 --> 02:22:00,140
It's a lie.
I cannot say it.

1308
02:22:14,260 --> 02:22:16,760
When can we begin to drill?
                  Very soon.

1309
02:22:16,760 --> 02:22:18,260
How long will it take
to bring in the well?

1310
02:22:18,260 --> 02:22:20,260
It shouldn't take long.

1311
02:22:20,270 --> 02:22:23,780
I would like
a $100,000
signing bonus,

1312
02:22:23,770 --> 02:22:27,270
plus the five
that is owed to me
with interest.

1313
02:22:27,770 --> 02:22:29,570
That's only fair.

1314
02:22:35,450 --> 02:22:39,950
I am a false prophet,
and God is a superstition.

1315
02:22:40,450 --> 02:22:43,370
If that's what you believe,
then I will say it.

1316
02:22:43,370 --> 02:22:45,370
Say it like you mean it.

1317
02:22:45,370 --> 02:22:47,370
Daniel.

1318
02:22:47,380 --> 02:22:49,720
Say it like
it's your sermon.

1319
02:22:52,630 --> 02:22:54,630
Don't smile.

1320
02:23:00,140 --> 02:23:02,140
I am a false prophet.

1321
02:23:02,140 --> 02:23:05,640
God is a superstition.
    Why don't you stand up?

1322
02:23:08,650 --> 02:23:10,650
Put your glass down.

1323
02:23:22,660 --> 02:23:26,660
I am a false prophet.

1324
02:23:26,670 --> 02:23:29,480
God is a superstition.
             Eli, stop.

1325
02:23:29,970 --> 02:23:32,970
Just imagine this
is your church here

1326
02:23:32,970 --> 02:23:35,470
and you have a full
congregation, so...

1327
02:23:37,480 --> 02:23:41,490
I am a false prophet.
God is a superstition.

1328
02:23:41,480 --> 02:23:44,310
Say it again.

1329
02:23:44,320 --> 02:23:48,330
I am a false prophet.
God is a superstition.

1330
02:23:48,320 --> 02:23:49,320
They can't hear you
at the back.

1331
02:23:49,320 --> 02:23:52,820
I am a false prophet.
God is a superstition.

1332
02:23:52,820 --> 02:23:54,320
Say it again.

1333
02:23:54,330 --> 02:23:58,840
I am a false prophet!
God is a superstition!

1334
02:23:58,830 --> 02:24:00,830
Say it again.

1335
02:24:00,830 --> 02:24:04,420
I am a false prophet!
God is a superstition!

1336
02:24:05,420 --> 02:24:07,920
Those areas
have been drilled.

1337
02:24:11,040 --> 02:24:12,540
What?

1338
02:24:12,540 --> 02:24:15,050
Those areas,
they've been drilled.

1339
02:24:16,550 --> 02:24:18,050
No, they haven't.

1340
02:24:18,050 --> 02:24:20,550
Yes, it's...

1341
02:24:20,550 --> 02:24:22,140
It's called drainage, Eli.

1342
02:24:22,140 --> 02:24:26,640
See, I own everything
around it, so, of course,
I get what's underneath it.

1343
02:24:28,140 --> 02:24:31,650
But there are no
derricks there.

1344
02:24:31,650 --> 02:24:34,150
This is the Bandy tract.
Do you understand?

1345
02:24:34,150 --> 02:24:36,650
Do you understand, Eli?

1346
02:24:36,650 --> 02:24:40,150
That's more to the point.
Do you understand?

1347
02:24:40,160 --> 02:24:46,170
I drink your water.
I drink it up every day.

1348
02:24:46,660 --> 02:24:50,660
I drink the blood of Lamb
from Bandy's tract.

1349
02:24:56,050 --> 02:24:58,220
You can sit down again.

1350
02:25:16,240 --> 02:25:17,740
Oh, Daniel.

1351
02:25:20,750 --> 02:25:21,760
Daniel.

1352
02:25:25,750 --> 02:25:27,250
Please.

1353
02:25:29,750 --> 02:25:32,260
I am in desperate times.

1354
02:25:32,260 --> 02:25:33,760
I know.

1355
02:25:34,260 --> 02:25:37,260
I need a friend.
  Yes. Of course, you do.

1356
02:25:37,260 --> 02:25:38,760
I've sinned.

1357
02:25:40,770 --> 02:25:43,780
I need help.
I'm a sinner.

1358
02:25:43,770 --> 02:25:48,770
I've let
the devil grab hold of me
in ways I never imagined.

1359
02:25:48,770 --> 02:25:50,020
I'm so full of sin.

1360
02:25:50,030 --> 02:25:53,540
The Lord sometimes
challenges us,
doesn't He, Eli?

1361
02:25:53,530 --> 02:25:55,530
Oh, yes, He does, Daniel.
             Yes, He does.

1362
02:25:55,530 --> 02:25:58,530
Yes, He does!

1363
02:25:58,530 --> 02:26:01,540
Yes, He does!

1364
02:26:01,540 --> 02:26:06,990
He's completely failed
to alert me to the recent
panic in our economy.

1365
02:26:07,490 --> 02:26:09,490
And this...
            Oh, dear.

1366
02:26:09,490 --> 02:26:16,500
I must have this, Daniel.
I must, I must,
I must have this.

1367
02:26:16,500 --> 02:26:18,500
My investments have...

1368
02:26:18,500 --> 02:26:24,010
Daniel, I won't bore you,
but if I could grab the
Lord's hand for help I would,

1369
02:26:24,010 --> 02:26:27,010
but He does these
things all the time.

1370
02:26:27,010 --> 02:26:31,010
These mysteries
that He presents,
and while we wait...

1371
02:26:32,020 --> 02:26:34,520
While we wait
for His word!

1372
02:26:34,520 --> 02:26:37,320
Because you're not
the chosen brother, Eli.

1373
02:26:39,820 --> 02:26:43,830
'Twas Paul
who was chosen.

1374
02:26:44,330 --> 02:26:47,330
He found me and told me
about your land.
You're just a fool.

1375
02:26:47,330 --> 02:26:48,830
Why are you
talking about Paul?

1376
02:26:48,830 --> 02:26:50,330
I did what your
brother couldn't.

1377
02:26:50,340 --> 02:26:52,850
Don't say this to me.
              I broke you
              and I beat you.

1378
02:26:53,840 --> 02:26:56,840
It was Paul
told me about you.

1379
02:26:56,840 --> 02:27:01,340
He's the prophet.
He's the smart one.
He knew what was there

1380
02:27:01,350 --> 02:27:03,860
and he found me
to take it out
of the ground.

1381
02:27:03,850 --> 02:27:07,850
Know what
the funny thing is?
Listen, listen.

1382
02:27:07,850 --> 02:27:12,860
I paid him $10,000
cash in hand.
Just like that.

1383
02:27:12,860 --> 02:27:16,360
He has his own company now.
Prosperous little business.

1384
02:27:16,360 --> 02:27:18,360
Three wells producing,
$5,000 a week.

1385
02:27:21,870 --> 02:27:25,870
Stop crying,
you sniveling ass.
Stop your nonsense.

1386
02:27:26,870 --> 02:27:29,870
You're just
the afterbirth, Eli.

1387
02:27:29,870 --> 02:27:30,870
No.

1388
02:27:30,880 --> 02:27:33,390
That slithered out
on your mother's filth.

1389
02:27:33,380 --> 02:27:34,880
No.

1390
02:27:34,880 --> 02:27:39,300
They should've put
you in a glass jar
on the mantelpiece.

1391
02:27:40,800 --> 02:27:44,300
Where were you
when Paul was suckling
at his mother's teat?

1392
02:27:44,310 --> 02:27:45,820
Where were you?

1393
02:27:46,310 --> 02:27:48,310
Who was nursing you,
poor Eli?

1394
02:27:48,810 --> 02:27:50,810
One of Bandy's sows?

1395
02:27:50,810 --> 02:27:53,810
That land has been had.
Nothing you can
do about it. It's gone.

1396
02:27:53,820 --> 02:27:56,330
If you would just
take this lease...
                    You lose.

1397
02:27:56,320 --> 02:27:59,320
Drainage!

1398
02:28:00,320 --> 02:28:04,320
Drainage, Eli, you boy.

1399
02:28:05,330 --> 02:28:08,330
Drained dry.
I'm so sorry.

1400
02:28:09,330 --> 02:28:11,330
If you have a milkshake

1401
02:28:12,330 --> 02:28:14,330
and I have a milkshake,

1402
02:28:14,340 --> 02:28:15,850
and I have a straw,
there it is.

1403
02:28:15,840 --> 02:28:17,840
That's the straw,
you see?

1404
02:28:17,840 --> 02:28:19,340
Watch it.

1405
02:28:20,840 --> 02:28:27,600
Now my straw
reaches across the room

1406
02:28:29,100 --> 02:28:31,600
and starts to
drink your milkshake.

1407
02:28:32,600 --> 02:28:36,610
I drink your milkshake!

1408
02:28:38,610 --> 02:28:40,110
I drink it up!

1409
02:28:40,110 --> 02:28:42,030
Don't bully me, Daniel.

1410
02:28:44,650 --> 02:28:47,150
Did you think
your song and dance

1411
02:28:47,150 --> 02:28:49,950
and your superstition
would help you, Eli?

1412
02:28:49,950 --> 02:28:55,160
I am the Third Revelation.
I am who the Lord has chosen.

1413
02:28:57,160 --> 02:28:59,410
Daniel!
Because I'm smarter
than you!

1414
02:28:59,410 --> 02:29:01,830
I'm older!

1415
02:29:01,830 --> 02:29:03,830
I'm your old friend,
Daniel!

1416
02:29:03,840 --> 02:29:05,930
I'm not a false prophet...
            Help me! Help me!

1417
02:29:06,420 --> 02:29:08,590
...you sniveling boy!

1418
02:29:08,590 --> 02:29:12,090
I am the Third Revelation!

1419
02:29:12,090 --> 02:29:15,260
I am the Third Revelation!

1420
02:29:15,260 --> 02:29:18,260
I told you
     I would eat you.
We're family!

1421
02:29:18,270 --> 02:29:20,780
I told you
I would eat you up!

1422
02:29:20,770 --> 02:29:23,270
We're brothers!
We're brothers!

1423
02:29:29,780 --> 02:29:32,780
Daniel, please forgive me.
I beg you.

1424
02:29:36,420 --> 02:29:38,700
That's it. That's it.

1425
02:30:41,100 --> 02:30:42,350
Mr. Daniel?

1426
02:30:50,160 --> 02:30:52,160
I'm finished.
